<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1886-10-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1886-10-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="180" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d180">
                    <head>No. 176.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Phelps</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1886-10-12"><hi rend="italic">October</hi> 12, 1886</date>.
                            [Received October 26.]</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 372.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inclose herewith a copy of
                        a note received by me this day from Lord Iddesleigh in reference to the
                        Canadian fisheries.</p>
                    <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer><signed>E. J. PHELPS.</signed></closer>
                    <frus:attachment>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure in Mr. Phelps’s No.
                            372.]</seg></opener>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Lord <persName type="from">Iddesleigh</persName> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">Phelps</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Foreign
                                        Office</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1886-10-11"><hi rend="italic">October</hi> 11,
                                1886</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 11th ultimo, on the subject of the Canadian
                            fisheries, and I beg leave to acquaint you that the note is under the
                            careful consideration of Her Majesty’s Government and that an answer
                            will be returned as early as possible.</p>
                        <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                        <closer><signed>IDDESLEIGH.</signed></closer>
                    </frus:attachment>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>